9:
All right. Time for some
reconnaissance. Nimbus, you're
coming with me.
13: Alk... What do you think of Zekhel?
16:
I don't think he's a bad guy. He's not
out to hurt anyone.
18:
But... he's got a dark side to him. I
don't think I trust him. Not yet.
21:
Hmm... Yes. All things considered, I
agree with your assessment.
24:
This entire affair could—and likely
will—turn political very fast. We still
have the option of stopping before
we're also implicated.
28:
At this point, we can back out and
escape whatever the Guild is
scheming. It will just mean giving up
on the information Dul Kugala
offered us.
34: But... What if this is all my fault?
37:
It is highly probable that Memram
and her people were brought here
due to the merging of worlds.
41:
And not only that. Everything that
has happened so far, it has all been—
45:
I understand, Stella. Even despite
that, I still think it would be okay for
us to wash our hands of this affair.
52:
I had a feeling you would react that
way. And I knew you'd be reluctant
to give up.
54:
But let me say this much:
The sense of duty and responsibility
that so torments you...
57:
You can toss it aside. You need not
be burdened by it. Nobody will
blame you.
61:
But I...
I don't want to run away.
64:
I understand.
If that's the case... then so be it.
67:
If it's what you truly desire, then I will
support you—just as you once
supported me.
71:
No matter how things play out, I will
always be on your side.
Remember that.
76:
I agree.
Nimbus isn't here, but I'm sure he'd
say the exact same thing.
86:
Everyone, get over here! We found
Memram.
90:
There, right below us. Don't poke
your head too far out.
95:
Memram's been doing that the
whole time. Something about this
looks off...
98:
That's a ritual if I've ever seen one...
But what are they trying to do?
106:
Hear me! Before you stand the
Vesta, bearers of the Spirit Horns.
I, Memram, am their Archon!
108:
Upon the authority of the stars, I
order you, sword!
Cut through the fabric of space!
114: Just what the hell are they doing?!
119:
They're controlling the distortions
and... summoning reinforcements?
That organization... Could they be
involved?!
121:
There's not that many of them... I
could probably clean this up all on
my own.
128:
Sorry, I can't just sit around and
allow a military force to run
rampant right underneath Palpebra.
133:
Wait! Some of them appear to be
wounded!
Wh-what is happening?
140:
Lady Memram!
Close the gate! Quickly!
154: You dare come before me, monster?!
168:
Screw these things!
We've got your back, sheep lady.
